Title: Fiddle Leaf Fig
Description:
Sunlight: Indirect bright light 
Water: When 50% of the soil is dry, then water until soil is moist

Title: Jade Bonsai

Title: Air Plant

Title: Bird of Paradise
Description: Give any room a hint of a tropical getaway with a bird of paradise plant! They are very easy to take care of. Just give it a sunny place by a window and water when the top of the soil feels dry. I got this plant 1 1/2 years ago and it has gotten 2 feet taller with not too much maintenance (though I do need to repot it!)

Title: Snake Plant
Description: Snake plants (mother in law's tongue) are resilient and make a statement. In my experience, they can grow in any pretty much any level of light  and need to be watered about once a week.

Title: Umbrella Plant
Description: This tropical plant has cute glossy leaves that droop like an umbrella. I instantly fell in love with the shape of this plant at the nursery. They need lots of indirect light and enjoy being misted with water.
